Document: Shape2D
Path: godot/classes/class_shape2d.rst
Summary: Base class for all 2D collision shapes.

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted

The Shape2D resource is the base class for all 2D collision shapes. It is used by physics bodies to define their collision boundaries.

This class does not have any methods or properties of its own, but it serves as a base for various shape types like CircleShape2D, RectangleShape2D, CapsuleShape2D, and others. Each of these derived classes provides specific geometric properties to define a collision shape.

Key Rule: All derived Shape2D resources are resources, meaning they can be saved and loaded independently of the nodes that use them.
