Document: Shape2D
Path: godot/classes/class_shape2d.rst
Summary: Abstract base class for all 2D shapes used in physics.
Abstract base class for all 2D shapes, intended for use in physics. Primitive shapes, especially CircleShape2D, are fast to check collisions against. ConvexPolygonShape2D is slower, and ConcavePolygonShape2D is the slowest.
---CHUNK---
Document: Shape2D
Path: godot/classes/class_shape2d.rst
Summary: This document provides an overview of the Shape2D class in Godot Engine, which serves as a base class for 2D physics shapes.

Shape2D is the base class for all 2D physics shapes in Godot. It is not intended to be used directly, but rather serves as a base for derived classes like CircleShape2D, RectangleShape2D, CapsuleShape2D, and ConcavePolygonShape2D. These derived classes define the actual geometry used for collision detection and physics simulation in Godot's 2D physics engine.

Inherits: Resource < Object

